## 1 Введение

На \(\mathbb{R}^{n}\) обозначим \(\nabla\) градиент и \(e^{t\,\Delta}\) (\(t>0\)) полу-группу ядра тепла. Мы видим, что \(\nabla\) и \(e^{t\,\Delta}\) коммутируют, т. е.

\[\nabla e^{t\Delta}f(g)=e^{t\Delta}(\nabla f)(g),\quad\forall g\in\mathbb{R}^{n},\ t>0,\ f\in C_{o}^{\infty}\big(\mathbb{R}^{n}\big).\]

В общем случае это свойство не сохраняется в рамках римановых многообразий, \((M,\,g_{M})\). Однако, если кривизна Риччи на \(M\), \(\mathrm{Ric}(M)\), минорирована числом \(k\) (\(k\in\mathbb{R}\)), то Д. Бакри показал в [4], что :

\[\big{|}\nabla e^{t\Delta}f(g)\big{|}\leqslant e^{-kt}e^{t\Delta}\big{(}|\nabla f|\big{)}(g),\quad\forall g\in M,\ t>0,\ f\in C_{o}^{\infty}(M).\]Когда кривизна Риччи на \(M\) имеет нижнюю границу, \(M\) является стохастически полной, т.е. \(e^{t\Delta}1=1\) для любого \(t>0\). Immediate consequence of (1.1) is that для любого \(1\leqslant w<+\infty\) we have

\[\big{|}\nabla e^{t\Delta}f(g)\big{|}\leqslant e^{-kt}\big{[}e^{t\Delta}\big{(}|\nabla f|^{w}\big{)}(g)\big{]}^{1/w},\quad\forall g\in M,\ t>0,\ f\in C_{o}^{\infty}(M),\]

or, more weakly,

\[\big{\|}\nabla e^{t\Delta}f\big{\|}_{L^{\infty}}\leqslant e^{-kt}\|\nabla f\|_{L^{ \infty}},\quad\forall t>0,\ f\in C_{o}^{\infty}(M).\]

Estimates of type (1.2) or in a weaker form (or stronger) have many applications, for example, in the study of Poincaré and Sobolev logarithmic inequalities for the heat semigroup, in the study of the criterion \(\varGamma_{2}\) and also in the study of Riesz transforms, see for example [1-3,7] and their references.

Recently, von Renesse and Sturm have shown that in the framework of complete Riemannian manifolds, the estimate (1.3) with \(k\in\mathbb{R}\) implies that \(\mathrm{Ric}(M)\geqslant k\), see [24]. For other results equivalent to the estimate (1.1), see for example [1,24] and their references.

And in [17] (see also [18]), it has been shown that the estimates (1.3) or (1.2) are no longer valid on conic manifolds. More precisely, on the cone \(C(S_{\vartheta})\) with \(\vartheta>2\pi\), which is a Riemannian manifold with zero sectional curvature but not complete, there exists a smooth function with compact support defined on \(C(S_{\vartheta})\), \(f_{o}\), such that \(\|\nabla e^{t\Delta}f_{o}\|_{L^{\infty}}=+\infty\) for any \(t>0\).

In [9], Driver and Melcher studied estimates of type (1.2) in the framework of the 3-dimensional Heisenberg group, \(\mathbb{H}^{1}\), which can be considered as a manifold equipped with a degenerate Laplacian.Напомним, см., например, [12, с. 98], что $\mathbb{H}^{1}=\mathbb{R}^{2}\times\mathbb{R}$ - это стратифицированная группа Ли для закона 

$$(x_{1},x_{2},t)\cdot(x_{1}^{\prime},x_{2}^{\prime},t^{\prime})=\big{(}x_{1}+x_{1}^{\prime},x_{2}+x_{2}^{\prime},t_{1}+t_{1}^{\prime}+2(x_{1}^{\prime}x_{2}-x_{1}x_{2}^{\prime})\big{)}.$$

И суб-Лапласиан на $\mathbb{H}^{1}$ записывается как

